Package provided.datapacket

Class DataPacket<T extends IDataPacketData,S>

  • java.lang.Object
    • provided.extvisitor.AExtVisitorHost<IDataPacketID,ADataPacket>
      • provided.datapacket.ADataPacket
        • provided.datapacket.DataPacket<T,S>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the data being held. T must be an INTERFACE extending IDataPacketData.
    S - The type of the sender object to which datapackets can be sent back to. * ---------------------------------------------- Adds the ability to hold IDataPacketData type data and have any type of sender.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, IExtVisitorHost<IDataPacketID,ADataPacket>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GroupDataPacket
    public class DataPacket<T extends IDataPacketData,S>
extends ADataPacket
    Concrete data packet that holds a generic type of data. Adds internal data content of type T and host ID type IDataPacketID;

    Stephen Wong (c) 2018

        Parameters:
